original: Jacobsson, Gösta Emanuel, e. o. hovrättsnotarie, Göteborg, f. 23/10/93 i Gbg av Gustaf Emil J, o. Alma Rho-din. — Stud:ex. 13, jur. kand. i Upps. 20. Tingstjg. 20-22, tjg. å statskont. o. nedre just irevisionsexp. 22-24, not. v. drätselikamtm. i Gbg sed. 24. Hoh-by: fotografering.
translated: Jacobsson, Gösta Emanuel, acting associate judge, Gothenburg, born on October 23, 1893 in Gothenburg to Gustaf Emil J and Alma Rhodin. He completed high school in 1913 and obtained a law degree from Uppsala University in 1920. He worked as a clerical officer between 1920-1922 and then worked at the State Audit Institution and the lower judicial revision authority between 1922-1924. He served as a notary public of the fiscal board in Gothenburg from 1924. He married but partner's name unknown. His hobby was photography.
